content: I just found out that in each trip, if I use both fuel and electric, I will not get a separate correct calculate for the consumption rate of each type. The app just simply uses the total milage / petrol used in liter then convert to mpg, it then uses the same total milage / electric usage to get mi/kWh. As a result, for a long journey, when electric is just used for a short distance, but l can even get a 14.6Mi/kWh, which normally is just around 3.8. I hope you can correct this calculation.
content_english: “I just found out that in each trip, if I use both fuel and electric, I will not get a separate correct calculation for the consumption rate of each type. The app just simply uses the total mileage / petrol used in liter then converts to mpg, it then uses the same total mileage / electric usage to get mi/kWh. As a result, for a long journey, when electric is just used for a short distance, but I can even get a 14.6Mi/kWh, which normally is just around 3.8. I hope you can correct this calculation.”

content_english: "Until last week, I could log in, but suddenly I can't log in anymore, and I'm in trouble because I can't use the navigation or settings. Thank you for your reply. I was able to grasp the situation a little more precisely through subsequent operations, so here's the details. It seems I can’t log in to MyBMW when the car is offline (when it's in a mechanically-operated parking garage where the signal doesn't reach). I was able to log in after the car was taken out of the garage for a few hours, but I was able to log in for a few hours after it was put back in the garage, but then it stopped working. It's a shame that I can’t use the app when the car is offline, because I can’t set the navigation destination before getting in the car."

content: 530eで使用中。 このアプリを使いだしてから、ディスプレイキーの出番がなくなりました。 充電状況や可能走行距離の確認、エアコンの乗車前での設定、目的地の登録や充電設備の検索など便利に使っています。 指紋認証で起動できるのも良い点です。 ただ、燃料の残が満タンにしても満タンマイナス3リッターなのは残念ですね。 施錠が出来るのですから、窓を閉めることもしてほしいです。また、トヨタ車のように施錠や窓が開いていることをメールかプッシュ通知で教えてくれると万全です。
content_english: Using this with my 530e. Since I started using this app, I no longer need the Display Key. I’m using it conveniently to check charging status and possible driving range, set the AC before getting in, register destinations, and search for charging stations. The fingerprint authentication startup is a good point. However, it’s a shame that even when the fuel level is full, it shows as full minus 3 liters. Since it can lock the car, I wish it would also close the windows. Also, it would be perfect if it could notify me via email or push notification when the car is locked or windows are open, like with Toyota cars.

content: The app missing basics. There is no option to inform you if you left the car unlocked or a windows open. Worst part is that, even when you open the app, there is no option to get an update from the car. It shows the last time the phone was in the car. Last few times it was showing that I had full tank (did not update for 2 days). The only way to get an update from the car is to unlock it from the car and lock it again. Allot must change for a service that is not even free!!
